/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 658.0 Tm (Abstract) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 644.0 Tm (Sourdough starters are often described as stable communities that reflect the bakery in) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 630.0 Tm (which they live. By sequencing the microbial composition of fourteen starters maintained for) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 616.0 Tm (between two and ninety years, we show that stability is partial and scale-dependent. A core) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 602.0 Tm (of lactic acid bacteria and a dominant yeast persist, but the minor membership drifts) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 588.0 Tm (continually, and the romantic claim that a starter carries the unbroken signature of its) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 574.0 Tm (founding decade is not supported by our data.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 542.0 Tm (Introduction) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 528.0 Tm (A sourdough starter is a small, portable ecosystem, and like any ecosystem it is subject to) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 514.0 Tm (invasion, succession, and drift. Bakers prize the idea that a starter is a living heirloom) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 500.0 Tm (whose microbial character has been faithfully handed down for generations. This study tests) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 486.0 Tm (how much of that character actually endures.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 472.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 458.0 Tm (We sampled fourteen starters of widely differing ages and geographic origins, sequencing) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 444.0 Tm (both their bacterial and fungal members. Our aim was to distinguish the stable core of a) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 430.0 Tm (starter from its mutable fringe, and to ask whether age leaves any detectable signature at) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 416.0 Tm (all.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 402.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 384.0 Tm (Sampling and Sequencing) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 370.0 Tm (Starters were sampled at peak activity, a fixed number of hours after refreshment, to) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 356.0 Tm (standardise the community state. Bakers supplied a maintenance history including refreshment) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 342.0 Tm (frequency, flour type, and ambient temperature, allowing us to relate composition to) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 328.0 Tm (husbandry.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 314.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 300.0 Tm (We characterised each community by amplicon sequencing of conserved marker regions for) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 286.0 Tm (bacteria and yeasts, and expressed membership as relative abundance. To probe stability,) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 272.0 Tm (four starters were resampled at three-month intervals across a full year.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 258.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 240.0 Tm (A Stable Core, A Mobile Fringe) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 226.0 Tm (Every starter was dominated by a small number of lactic acid bacteria and a single principal) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 212.0 Tm (yeast, and this dominant guild was remarkably consistent across the collection. At this) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 198.0 Tm (coarse level, starters do look stable and even interchangeable, which explains the) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 184.0 Tm (durability of the 'living heirloom' narrative.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 170.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 156.0 Tm (Beneath the core, however, the picture dissolved. The minor membership, the species present) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 142.0 Tm (at low abundance, turned over substantially between resampling points within a single) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 128.0 Tm (starter, often more than it differed between two unrelated starters. Husbandry, especially) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 114.0 Tm (refreshment frequency and temperature, predicted composition far better than age did.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 100.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 82.0 Tm (What Age Does and Does Not Preserve) Tj
