/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 736.0 Tm (We could find no reliable microbial marker of a starter's age. A ninety-year-old culture and) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 722.0 Tm (a two-year-old culture maintained under similar conditions converged on similar communities,) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 708.0 Tm (while the same starter shifted noticeably when its owner moved house and changed flour. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 694.0 Tm (starter remembers its current keeper, not its founder.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 680.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 666.0 Tm (This does not diminish the cultural value of an old starter, but it does relocate that) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 652.0 Tm (value. What persists across generations is the practice of maintenance, not a fixed) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 638.0 Tm (microbial lineage. The community is continually rebuilt to fit present conditions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 624.0 Tm () Tj
/F2 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 606.0 Tm (Conclusion) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 592.0 Tm (Long-maintained sourdoughs are stable in their dominant members and fluid in everything) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 578.0 Tm (else. Their composition tracks current husbandry rather than founding date, and the notion) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 564.0 Tm (of an unbroken microbial signature stretching back decades is a story about people, not) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 550.0 Tm (about the bacteria. For RAG purposes this article pairs usefully with the soil-microbiology) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 536.0 Tm (entry as a contrast in how 'community stability' is claimed and tested.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 522.0 Tm () Tj
